{% layout false %}
{%- comment -%}
  Operator guide for cms/blog (English).

  URL: /s/about (statics/about.liquid).
  Related: Brand tokens at /s/brand (statics/brand.liquid).
{%- endcomment -%}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html class="scroll-smooth" lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="author" content="Baklib">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Theme Guide · {{ site.name }}</title>
    {% meta_tags %}
    {% render 'theme_runtime_colors' %}
    {{ 'stylesheets/application.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag: data-turbo-track: 'reload' }}
    {{ 'baklib/shared/main.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag: data-turbo-track: 'reload' }}
    {{ 'baklib/shared/main.js' | asset_url | script_tag: data-turbo-track: 'reload' }}
    {{ 'javascripts/application.js' | asset_url | script_tag: defer: true, data-turbo-track: 'reload' }}

    <style>
      .about-anchor { scroll-margin-top: 5rem; }
      .about-prose h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.025em; color: var(--color-accent); }
      .about-prose h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-base-content) 55%, transparent); }
      .about-prose p { margin-top: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.6; color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-base-content) 80%, transparent); }
      .about-prose ul, .about-prose ol { margin-top: 0.5rem; padding-left: 1.25rem; color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-base-content) 80%, transparent); }
      .about-prose li { margin-top: 0.3rem; line-height: 1.55; }
      .about-prose code { border-radius: 0.25rem; background: var(--color-base-200); padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem; font-size: 0.875em; color: var(--color-accent); }
      .about-prose pre { margin-top: 0.75rem; overflow-x: auto; border-radius: var(--radius-box); border: 1px solid var(--color-base-300); background: var(--color-base-200); padding: 0.875rem 1rem; font-size: 0.7rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--color-accent); }
      .about-prose pre code { background: transparent; padding: 0; color: inherit; }
      .about-prose a:not(.btn) { font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-primary); text-underline-offset: 2px; }
      .about-prose a:not(.btn):hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body class="min-h-screen bg-base-100 text-base-content antialiased">
    {%- assign nav_links = "overview,managers,developers,resources" | split: "," -%}
    {%- assign nav_labels = "Overview,Managers,Developers,Resources" | split: "," -%}

    <header class="sticky top-0 z-20 border-b border-base-300/70 bg-base-100/85 backdrop-blur">
      <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-3xl items-center justify-between gap-3 px-4 py-3 sm:px-6">
        <a href="{{ site.index_path }}" class="flex min-w-0 items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold tracking-tight text-accent">
          <span class="inline-flex size-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-box bg-primary text-primary-content">
            {% render 'icon', name: 'book-open', class: 'size-4' %}
          </span>
          <span class="truncate">{{ site.name }}</span>
        </a>
        <nav class="hidden items-center gap-0.5 text-xs sm:flex sm:text-sm">
          {%- for link in nav_links -%}
            <a href="#{{ link }}" class="rounded-field px-2.5 py-1 text-base-content/70 hover:bg-base-200 hover:text-base-content">{{ nav_labels[forloop.index0] }}</a>
          {%- endfor -%}
        </nav>
        <a href="/s/brand" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm shrink-0">Brand</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="about-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pb-20 sm:px-6">

      <section class="py-10 sm:py-14">
        <p class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-selector bg-base-200 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-base-content/60">
          <span class="size-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
          cms/blog · v2.0.2
        </p>
        <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-accent sm:text-3xl">
          Blog Theme Guide
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-2 max-w-xl text-sm text-base-content/70">
          Quick reference for running a blog, news, or announcements site on Baklib with the
          <strong>blog</strong> template. Static URL: <code>/s/about</code>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="overview" class="about-anchor border-t border-base-300 pt-10">
        <h2>1. Overview</h2>

        <h3>Template name</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>blog</strong> (<code>themes/cms/blog</code>) — Baklib CMS scope, version
          <code>2.0.2</code>. Stack: Tailwind CSS v4, daisyUI v5, Turbo + Stimulus, Lucide icons.
        </p>

        <h3>Purpose</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Publish time-ordered articles, release notes, and announcements.</li>
          <li>Let visitors browse by tags, search, and read rich article pages.</li>
          <li>Give editors two home layouts (card grid vs. compact list) without changing the article template.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Hero-led home with tag toolbar and publish-date sorting on the card layout.</li>
          <li>Admin-driven theme colors mapped at runtime to daisyUI semantic tokens.</li>
          <li>Sticky site header plus article breadcrumb bar with page tools (copy link, etc.).</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Storefront templates</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm">
          <li><code>index</code> / <code>index.list</code> — home (card grid or list)</li>
          <li><code>page</code> — article with cover, body, child cards, optional feedback</li>
          <li><code>tag</code>, <code>search</code> — tag archive and site search</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="managers" class="about-anchor border-t border-base-300 pt-10">
        <h2>2. For content managers</h2>

        <ol>
          <li>
            <strong>Create a site</strong> — In the template marketplace, select the
            <strong>blog</strong> template to start a new CMS site.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Configure the site</strong> — In admin: site language, theme colors (recommended palettes in theme settings), home page dynamic fields (title, description, hero image), custom domain, Feedback form toggle, and access control as needed. Wire header/footer menus via <code>header_menu_html</code> / <code>footer_menu_html</code> in theme settings.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Publish content</strong> — Add child pages under home, choose the <strong>Page</strong> template, fill dynamic fields (title, cover, body, tags), then publish and preview. Switch the home page template between <code>index</code> (cards) and <code>index.list</code> (list + search) anytime.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-base-content/60">
          Site tags are created in admin (not in theme settings). Attach them on articles via the page template <code>tag_picker</code> field. Seed sample menus live in <code>seeds/001_site.yml</code>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="developers" class="about-anchor border-t border-base-300 pt-10">
        <h2>3. For developers</h2>

        <h3>Baklib CMS templates</h3>
        <p>
          Theme development conventions (Liquid layout, objects, static routes, seeds) are documented in the
          <strong>baklib-theme-dev</strong> agent skill — path <code>/baklib-theme-dev</code> in the Baklib repo
          (not a public URL). Platform API and Liquid reference:
          <a href="https://dev.baklib.cn" rel="noopener noreferrer">dev.baklib.cn</a>.
        </p>

        <h3>File tree (concise)</h3>
        <pre><code>cms/blog/
├── config/settings_schema.json
├── layout/theme.liquid, error.liquid
├── templates/
│   ├── index.liquid          # home — card grid
│   ├── index.list.liquid     # home — list + search
│   ├── page.liquid, tag.liquid, search.liquid
│   └── feedback_*.liquid
├── snippets/
│   ├── _index_hero.liquid
│   ├── _tags_toolbar.liquid, _card_grid.liquid, _list.liquid
│   ├── _breadcrumb.liquid, _header.liquid, _footer.liquid
│   ├── _theme_runtime_colors.liquid, _icon.liquid
│   └── …
├── statics/about.liquid, brand.liquid, tags.liquid, recent.liquid
├── seeds/001_site.yml, 002_pages.yml
├── src/ → built to assets/ (npm run build)
└── locales/*.json</code></pre>

        <h3>Key implementation spots</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><code>_index_hero</code> — home hero from page variables <code>title</code>, <code>description</code>, <code>hero_image_url</code>; omitted when all empty.</li>
          <li><code>index</code> vs <code>index.list</code> — card grid uses <code>tags_toolbar</code> + <code>pages_in_list</code> by publish date; list home uses inline search, tag tabs, and <code>children_in_list</code>.</li>
          <li><code>_tags_toolbar</code> — tag pills and sort query on card home and tag template (<code>?sort=published_desc|published_asc</code>).</li>
          <li><code>_breadcrumb</code> + <code>_header</code> — fixed site header; second sticky bar on articles with trail + page tools (Stimulus).</li>
          <li><code>_theme_runtime_colors</code> — maps <code>--theme-color-*</code> to daisyUI <code>--color-*</code>; sets <code>--header-height</code>.</li>
          <li><code>_card_grid</code> — shared card for home, tag archive, and child-page grids.</li>
          <li><code>seeds/</code> — demo language, menus (including <code>/s/about</code>), hero defaults, sample articles.</li>
          <li><code>statics/brand.liquid</code> — visual token gallery at <code>/s/brand</code> (standalone layout, brand defaults inlined).</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-base-content/60">
          Pagination example (escaped): <code>&#123;% paginate_tag pages_in_list, per: 9 %&#125;</code>.
          After editing <code>src/</code>, run <code>npm run build</code> before committing built assets.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="resources" class="about-anchor border-t border-base-300 pt-10">
        <h2>4. Resources</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/s/brand">Brand guidelines</a> — <code>/s/brand</code> · colors, radius, components for this theme.</li>
          <li><a href="https://dev.baklib.cn" rel="noopener noreferrer">dev.baklib.cn</a> — CMS templates, Liquid objects, API.</li>
          <li><a href="https://help.baklib.cn/themes" rel="noopener noreferrer">help.baklib.cn/themes</a> — theme help center.</li>
          <li>Repo: <code>README.md</code> (English), <code>README.zh-CN.md</code> (maintainer notes).</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
          Other static routes: <code>/s/tags</code>, <code>/s/recent</code>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <footer class="mt-10 border-t border-base-300 pt-5 text-center text-xs text-base-content/50">
        Baklib · cms/blog · <a href="{{ site.index_path }}" class="text-primary">Back to site</a>
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
